        <mxCell id="W8-PMEAiIVXDEVYCgA4Y-63" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Discussion&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;The architecture of the system is a primary factor in determining the &lt;br/&gt;maintainability of the system. In the presented (very simplified) &lt;br/&gt;example, there are some positives and more interestingly some negative &lt;br/&gt;design patterns.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="300" x="80" y="900" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="W8-PMEAiIVXDEVYCgA4Y-64" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Positives&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Simplicity:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;Because the example system is &lt;b&gt;very&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;simple, it is not very difficult to find out which parts are responsible for possible emerging issues. Although the simplicity is very much caused by lack of features&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="300" x="440" y="900" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="W8-PMEAiIVXDEVYCgA4Y-65" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Negatives&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scalability:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;By following the provided diagram, the scalability of the system will become a glaring issue when the amount of concurrent users rises. This is caused by the monolithic desing of the backend and the database.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="150" width="300" x="800" y="900" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
